definition.value: Irregular, small-amplitude myoclonic movements of the hands and/or fingers on keeping outstretched posture (jerky postural tremor). Polyminimyoclonus is stimulus-sensitive and accentuated during voluntary movements. A cortical origin can be demonstrated by back-averaging techniques, and somatosensory evoked potentials (SSEPs) are sometimes giant. This term includes facial-faucial-finger minimyoclonus observed in Kufor-Rakeb syndrome.

value.value: A Hoffmann test is performed by flicking the fingernail of the long finger, from dorsal to volar, on each hand while the hand was supported by the examiner's hand. The test was done with the neck in the neutral position and then with the neck maximally forward flexed. Any flexion of the ipsilateral thumb and/or index finger was interpreted as a positive test.

value.value: Hoffmanův test se provádí tak, že se na každé ruce přejede přes nehet prostředníku (či do něj cvrnkne) z dorzální k volární straně, zatímco ruka je podepřena rukou vyšetřujícího. https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0031994 (Bronchial breath sound)  ; abnormality of the respiratory system

value.value: Bronchial breath sounds contain much higher frequency components than normal breath sounds due to alteration of the low pass filtering function of the alveoli, as occurs in consolidation. It is loud, hollow, and high pitch. Expiratory phase is longer than inspiratory phase with the inspiratory-expiratory ratio (I:E) changing from normal 3:1 to 1:2. There is distinct pause between inspiration and expiration due to absent alveolar phase. It is associated with whispering pectoriloquy.

Bronchiální dechové zvuky obsahují mnohem vyšší frekvenční složky než normální dechové zvuky v důsledku změny filtrační funkce dolní propusti alveolů, k níž dochází při konsolidaci. Jsou hlasité, duté a mají vysoký tón. Expirační fáze je delší než inspirační, přičemž poměr inspirace a exspirace (I:E) se mění z normálního poměru 3:1 na 1:2. Mezi vdechem a výdechem je zřetelná pauza způsobená absencí alveolární fáze. Je spojena s šeptavým pektoriokvilem.

value.value: Bronşiyal solunum sesleri konsolidasyonda meydana geldmesi üzerine alveollerin düşük geçiş filtrelemesi değişimlerine bağlı olarak normal solunum seslerinden çok daha yüksek frekans bileşenlerini içermektedir. Yüksek sesli, boş ve yüksek perdelidir. Ekspiratuvar fazı inspiratuvar-ekspiratuvar (I:E) oranının normal 3:1'den 2:1'e değiştiği inspiratuvar fazından daha uzundur. Alveoler fazın yokluğundan dolayı inspirasyon ve ekspirasyon arasında belirgin bir duraksama vardır. Fısıldayan pektoriloki ile ilişkilidir

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0031995 (Squawks)  ; abnormality of the respiratory system

value.value: Ciyaklamalar 200 ms'den kısa süren ve gıcırtı olarak da bilinen kısa inspiratuvar hırıltılardır. Akustik analizler temel frekansın 200 ve 300 Hz arasında değiştiğini gösterir. Ciyaklamalar genellikle geç inspirasyonda meydana gelir ve sıklıkla geç inspiratuvar rallerden önce gelir

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Squawks are short inspiratory wheezes of less than 200 ms duration and are also known as squeaks. Acoustic analysis shows the fundamental frequency varying between 200 and 300 Hz. Squawks usually occur in late inspiration and are often preceded by late inspiratory crackles.

value.value: Pískoty jsou krátké vdechové sípání o délce méně než 200 ms. Akustická analýza ukazuje, že základní frekvence se pohybuje mezi 200 a 300 Hz. Pískoty se obvykle objevují v závěru nádechu a často jim předchází pozdní inspirační krepitus.

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0031999 (Expiratory crackles)  ; abnormality of the respiratory system

value.value: Krepitus, který se objevuje během expirace

definition.value: Crackles are predominantly inspiratory in nature, but can also occur during expiration. It has been described in COPD, bronchiectasis, and IPF. One theory of the pathogenesis of expritory crackles states that some airways collapse during early expiration and air trapping develops. As expiration progresses, the pressure in the trapped region gradually increase, leading to a widened pressure difference across the airways. Once this pressure difference reaches the critical opening pressure, the airway pops open during expiration, producing crackles.

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0032000 (Pleural rub)  ; abnormality of the respiratory system

value.value: Abnormální vedlejší dechový fenomén, který je nemuzikální, krátký a prudký. Je škrábavého, drásavého a vrzajícího charakteru, vyskytuje se v obou fázích dýchání. Exspirační složka obvykle kopíruje složku inspirační. Vzniká v důsledku vzájemného tření obou listů pleury během dýchání. Z klinického hlediska je důležité odlišit ji od krepitu.

It occurs due to inflamed pleural surface rubbing each other during breathing. Clinically, it is important to differentiate it from crackles

definition.value: In most cases of hemidystonia, a contralateral structural lesion of the basal ganglia or thalamus can be demonstrated by neuroimaging. Common aetiologies include stroke and trauma, and younger patients seem to have a greater propensity to develop hemidystonia after cerebral insults. There is often a latency between cerebral injury and the onset of dystonia. Hemidystonia may be preceded by ipsilateral hemiparesis which often resolves as hemidystonia develops.

value.value: Heteroforie jsou latentní odchylky, které jsou řízeny fúzí. Za určitých okolností (specifické zrakové úkoly, únava, nemoc atd.) již nelze fúzi udržet a dochází k dekompenzaci.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Heterophorias are latent deviations that are controlled by fusion. In certain circumstances (specific visual tasks, fatigue, illness, etc.), fusion can no longer be maintained and decompensation occurs.

definition.value: Heterophorias are latent deviations that are controlled by fusion. In certain circumstances (specific visual tasks, fatigue, illness, etc.), fusion can no longer be maintained and decompensation occurs.

value.value: Heterotopiler füzyon ile kontrol edilen geç sapmalardır. Belli durumlarda (özel görsel iş, halsizlik, hastalık vb) füzyon devam ettirilemez ve dekompansasyon meydana gelir

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Heterophorias are latent deviations that are controlled by fusion. In certain circumstances (specific visual tasks, fatigue, illness, etc.), fusion can no longer be maintained and decompensation occurs.

definition.value: In contrast to heterophoria, heterotropias are manifest deviations. Some individuals may be phoric in one situation (e.g. for distance) and tropic in another (e.g. for near). The distinction between heterotropia and heterophoria is that heterotropia refers to a misalignment of the eyes when the affected individual is looking at an object while the eyes are uncovered whereas heterophoria is a misalignment that is observed only when the two eyes are no longer looking at the same object. The monocular cover-uncover test is the most important test for detecting the presence of manifest strabismus and for differentiating a heterophoria from a heterotropia.
